The author of the article, Jake Hemme, discusses his experience as a White House intern in the Office of the Staff Secretary. He explains that the office plays a vital role in the day-to-day operations of President Donald Trump's Administration, overseeing the flow of information into the Oval Office and ensuring that all relevant voices are included in policy decisions. Hemme, as the only intern in the office, has the opportunity to see all aspects of its work, including editing documents and tracking executive order directives. He expresses gratitude for the chance to be a part of the Administration's efforts to improve the lives of Americans.